  m_text: "Relatively inexpensive, the medium of charcoal made it possible for Lee
    Bae to explore various aspects of its materiality. He no longer felt displaced
    or uprooted when painting with charcoal. In his artistic practice, he found a
    way to connect with his cultural root. In this world of black and white, certain
    themes of Lee Bae\u2019s past re-emerged, including charcoal ink, calligraphy,
    and his own childhood."
